Feb 10 2006	Cheap and clean. Good value.	Stayed here for three nights in two rooms. Gave us next door to each other, and with a car full of luggage, parking 6 feet from our front door was unbeatable. Booked in UK with click4hotel and got it for a total of £92 for 3 nights in 2 rooms. Can never beat that. Slept in room approx 4-7pm and early am to about 7 am. Its what Vegas is all about. Rooms very basic and a little dark. But they were clean and beds were comfortable with linen changed daily. No worries about location as its 5-7 mins walk to the Trop/NYNY/MGM. We walked every night. It would prob take this long to get to your room from the Casino in a lot of the Strip hotels!! Contrary to other reviews, saw no unsavoury loiterers and felt pretty safe. Front reception has complimetary coffee, microwave and refrigerator use. Will stay again.	
Jan 2 2006	Here for gambling and adventure	We travelled from the UK and stayed at this hotel in mid-December 2005 having booked through last-minute.com. If you are in Vegas and your main aim is to gamble and explore the wider area, then this place is a good bet for the money. The hotel is 2 mins drive from the airport and you can park outside your room. There is a resturant (coco's) at the edge of the hotel which serves an excellent breakfast. Our room offered clean and comfortable accommodation. If you are flying in to Vegas I would personally always rent a car as this will allow you to make the most of all the sights and sounds Vegas and the surrounding country has to offer.	
Oct 24 2005	Worst hotel stay ever...	We originally stayed at the hotel in October 2004 and left with a poor impression. We notified the manager and expressed our concerns about the state and cleanliness of the property. We received a response from the manager saying that the property was in the process of going through a renovation and many of the rooms had been upgraded. It was possible we had stayed in an older room. He offered us a complimentary stay on our next visit to Las Vegas. Despite our better judgement, we booked a room in October 2005 hoping that the property had indeed been upgraded. When we checked into the room, we found it in the same or worse condition that the first room. Carpets were extremely dirty (after taking off shoes and walking around room, white socks were a dark brown color). Room smelled of cigarette smoke despite its designation as a smoke-free room. Double beds were extremely small and lumpy, and we discovered bugs in one bed the following morning. Bathroom was mildewy and plaster was peeling from walls. Hot water was intermittant. I would definitely NOT recommend this hotel under any circumstances.	
Oct 13 2005	A cheap and convenient place from which to see Vegas	This hotel is excellently located (about 5 mins walk from the strip). It is also very cheap - a key element if you're planning on doing some gambling! If you're a hotel snob then don't stay here because it's fairly basic. However, I found it acceptably clean and comfortable. You can also park right outside your door. The pool is nice, the staff friendly and there's a good place for breakfast (Cocos) round the corner. The only issues I had were that the air conditioning unit was a bit noisy and neither the bath nor sink had plugs.	
