Oct 19 2004	Good place for the price	My husband and I stayed at this hotel a few weeks ago when we had to come to Vegas for a funeral. We wanted to stay by the strip to make the vacation the best it could be. The first night we stayed at the Motel 6 right next door, the next night the Rodeway Inn. I have to say I enjoyed the Motel 6 much better if I had to choose. The Rodeway Inn wasn't terrible, the staff were extremely nice, even holding our funeral flowers in the back until our room was ready, but we had requested a non-smoking room with 1 bed and we got 2 beds and a smoking room. When we asked for a change they couldn't give it to us, I was really scared because I am allergic to cigarette smoke but luckly the room only had a faint smell. The bathrooms were dirty, I felt better wearing flip flops in the tubs and I had a misterious itching sensation as I was falling asleep in the bed. For me I personally wouldn't stay there again, I would choose the Motel 6, but dont be to scared if its the only place left to stay!	
Oct 13 2004	Excellent Position - Excellent Price	We stayed at this hotel during the Labor Day Long Weekend September 2004.We had previously stayed here during a Contiki trip back in 2000, and had especially sourced our accommodation here again for this trip.We booked online at a last minute accommodation website, and received the excellent rate of $29 a night, and $129 for the Labor Day Saturday night which we thought was a bit pricy, but understood that rates increase for weekends, especially during holiday periods.We would most defintely stay here again. The hotel is only a 6-8 minute walk to the MGM Grand and the strip. Is close to the Sam Remo hotel and there is a Carrows Restuarant onsite which offers reasonably priced quality meals (although you do have to try one of the Las Vegas Resort/Casino buffets at least once - Excalibur is a favourite for us).Dont expect too much in the way of the comforts of home though. The rooms are pretty plain and smallish, especially if you have 2 double beds like we did, although the bathroom is a good size.The staff are quite friendly, although after reading some of the other reviews here and what we observed whilst we were there, it seems that there are quite a few reservations made through online booking sites which dont seem to register in the Rodeway system. We had no problems though.We found the area quite safe, even at night but we wouldnt wander too much further from the strip than the area we were staying in.This hotels rating is heavily influenced by its excellent proximity to the Strip and the special rate we managed to get online.	
Oct 5 2004	Bargain basement bungalow	This is truly a place to crash and shower for the Las Vegas visitor who spends all his/her time out gambling and partying. Don't expect any luxuries like a hair dryer or a clock radio or even a little courtesy bottle of shampoo or hangars in the coat closet. One thin sheet on the mattress ... the electronic key stopped working the 2nd time I used it ... quite a mold collection around the bathtub. All for only $38 a night, tax included. Glad it was only one night!Quick walk to the San Remo, Tropicana, MGM and NYNY ... get while the gettin's good!	
Sep 27 2004	Great Location But Don't Expect Too Much	Rodeway Motel is located about a block and a half from the Strip, and next to Motel 6-- so look for the Big Motel 6 sign along Tropicana Avenue when you try to find it. It is directly behind Carrows Restaurant. It is very close and on the same side of Tropicana Avenue as the San Remo and the Tropicana Hotel and Casinos. Watch out for the traffic, because a lot of cars travel at highway speeds even though the sidewalks are located very close to the road. The Rodeway staff was very friendly and helpful, but I had a problem checking in when the desk clerk told me that my confirmed reservation from expedia was not confirmed on the Rodeway computer and that the motel was full. After about twenty minutes, the desk clerk found me a room, but advised me to call the motel next time to confirm my room reservation, even if I get an e-mail informing me that I have a confirmed room reservation. I'm just glad I brought the e-mail and my bank statement that proved that I did have a confirmed and already paid for room reservation. The room was very basic, so don't expect too much if you stay there. I found it satisfactory, but barely. It had clean linen, basic furnishings, plenty of hot water, abundant towels and washcloths, toilet paper, and soap, but the owners should seriously think about buying new furniture. The furniture looked like it was installed in the 1970's. Bring your own shampoo, or buy it at Walgreens or CVS on the Strip, because Rodeway doesn't furnish any. The motel is in a safe location, in terms of crime, but watch for speeding cars, and definitely don't jaywalk. The convenience store and restaurant in front of Rodeway are definite pluses. If you want a quality room, go to Bellagio, Caesar's Palace, Mandalay Bay, or the Venetian. If you only want a basic and cheap room to sleep in in a convenient and safe location, the Rodeway Motel will provide it if your expectations aren't too high.	
Sep 18 2004	Pleasantly Surprised!!!	I stayed 2 nights at the Rodeway Inn Sept. 15-17th and was a little nervous on arrival. The outside is not very impressive and there is a certain amount of trailer trash eliment around the area, but the front desk people are very friendly and helpful, I was even upgraded to a Suite (which I highly reccomend you reserve instead) when the clerk had trouble checking me into my reserved room. The suite was very large 1bdrm with full bath, clean sheets and towels everyday plus two t.v.'s a fridge and microwave also provided. There is a 24hr mini mart next door plus Carrows restaurant if you want to avoid long food lines at the Casino's which I did. I would highly recommend to couples or singles looking for a bargain motel in a great location.	
Sep 1 2004	Not Bad at all!!	I was wary of staying here from the reviews Ive seen on tripadvisor, but I took my chances.Its not bad at all, it doesnt look all that great, but it was clean, air conditioners, clean sheets and nice staff. They let me check in at 9 am, which was a huge help and much appreciated. I couldnt beat it for 50.00 a night. When your in vegas how much time do you actually spend in your room, just be sure to bring your own clock/alarm, they dont provide one.	
